Element ui:panel
Namespace https://github.com/bordertech/wcomponents/namespace/ui/v1.0
Annotations
 
WPanel provides a generic content container and a number of special purpose container and layout components. It is a fundamental UI layout
tool.

Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
accessKey restriction of xs:string optional 
Sets a single modified key access key for a control. This attribute should be used with caution as:<ul>
  <li>some user agents reserve some keys for internal use and do not expose them to the client for use as access keys; and</li>
  <li>some keys may clash or cause issues with use of various assistive technologies.</li>
</ul>
buttonId xs:NMTOKEN optional 
Provides the id of a WButton which can be used as a default submit button for all data-input components in the panel which support form
submission on ENTER key press. May be overridden by individual controls which implement a similar attribute.
hidden xs:boolean optional 
The component will be in a hidden state if "true". Not output if "false".
id xs:ID required 
The unique identifier for the component.
mode restriction of xs:NMTOKEN optional 
Indicates the content display mode for the component
title xs:string optional 
A human readable title for the panel. Required for @type "action" and "chrome" but optional otherwise.
track xs:boolean optional 
Indicates that the component should take part in web analytics tracking.
type restriction of xs:NMTOKEN optional 
Indicates the semantic meaning and/or stylistic options to be applied to the panel. Some types provide for explicit block level semantics and
style and others are merely stylistic.

Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
cols xs:unsignedInt required 
Indicates the number of columns to render in the grid. A value of zero indicates fixed rows, variable columns depending on
content.
hgap xs:positiveInteger optional 
The horizontal space between content components in the layout in pixels. This may be adjusted by the theme and/or user agent.
rows xs:unsignedInt required 
Indicates the number of rows to render in the grid. A value of zero indicates fixed columns, variable rows depending on
content.
vgap xs:positiveInteger optional 
The vertical space between content components in the layout in pixels. This may be adjusted by the theme and/or user agent.

Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
align restriction of xs:NMTOKEN required 
Indicates the flow arrangement
hgap xs:positiveInteger optional

valign restriction of xs:NMTOKEN optional

Element ui:panel / ui:columnLayout
Namespace https://github.com/bordertech/wcomponents/namespace/ui/v1.0
Annotations
 
Provides a layout mechanism for WPanel which attempts to apply a consistent row and column set to the components in the panel. This
differs from a grid layout in that the columns are not constrained to a uniform width or horizontal alignment of content.
Diagram
Properties
content complex
Model
ui:column+ , ui:cell*
Children ui:cell, ui:column

Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
hgap xs:positiveInteger optional

vgap xs:positiveInteger optional 
The vertical space between content components in the layout in pixels. This may be adjusted by the theme and/or user agent.

    <xs:documentation>Provides a layout mechanism for WPanel which attempts to apply a consistent row and column set to the components in the panel. This differs from a grid layout in that the columns are not constrained to a uniform width or horizontal alignment of content.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
  <xs:complexType>
    <xs:sequence>
      <xs:element name="column" maxOccurs="unbounded">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Provides information for the rendering of each column in the layout.</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
        <xs:complexType>
          <xs:attribute name="width" use="required">
            <xs:annotation>
              <xs:documentation>The width of the column as a percentage ofthe available space.</xs:documentation>
            </xs:annotation>
            <xs:simpleType>
              <xs:restriction base="xs:int">
                <xs:minInclusive value="1"/>
                <xs:maxInclusive value="100"/>
              </xs:restriction>
            </xs:simpleType>
          </xs:attribute>
          <xs:attribute name="align">
            <xs:annotation>
              <xs:documentation>The alignment of content in the column. if not set "left" is assumed.</xs:documentation>
            </xs:annotation>
            <xs:simpleType>
              <xs:restriction base="xs:token">

                  <xs:annotation>
                    <xs:documentation>The components in the column should be left aligned.</xs:documentation>
                  </xs:annotation>
                </xs:enumeration>

                  </xs:annotation>

                <xs:enumeration value="right">
                  <xs:annotation>
                    <xs:documentation>The components in the column should be right aligned.</xs:documentation>
                  </xs:annotation>
                </xs:enumeration>
              </xs:restriction>
            </xs:simpleType>
          </xs:attribute>
        </xs:complexType>
